That means any whole number or decimal can be written as a fraction with a bottom value or <strong>denominator</strong> of 1.</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p>&nbsp;</p>","rightText":"<p>`2/3xx819.75 = 2/3xx819.75/1`</p>"},{"settings":{"showAudio":1,"showNext":1,"showHeader":0,"hideRightPanel":0,"delayStep":"0","delayRight":"0","audioPath":"6"},"leftText":"<p>Multiply the values on top of both fractions (<strong>numerators</strong>) and the values on the bottom of both fractions (<strong>denominators</strong>).<br />&nbsp;</p>","rightText":"<p>`2/3xx819.75/1=(2xx819.75)/(3xx1)=1639.5/3`</p>"},{"settings":{"showAudio":1,"showNext":1,"showHeader":0,"hideRightPanel":0,"delayStep":"0","delayRight":"0","audioPath":"7"},"leftText":"<p>Divide.<br />&nbsp;</p>","rightText":"<p>`1639.5/3=546.5`</p>"},{"settings":{"showAudio":1,"showNext":1,"showHeader":0,"hideRightPanel":0,"delayStep":0,"delayRight":0,"audioPath":"8"},"leftText":"<p>Round if necessary.<br /><br />The original information says to round to the nearest cent, which is the same as rounding to 2 decimal places.<br />&nbsp;</p><table border=\"0\" cellpadding=\"1\" cellspacing=\"1\" class=\"ju-powertip\" style=\"width: 90%;\"><thead><tr><th scope=\"col\">DID YOU KNOW?&nbsp;
